values: Ugh.  How about a full day of lifting stuff...only to wake up and lift more the next day?  Well...I'd much rather lift stuff and move it with no pressure.  Thats no big deal to me.  I'm nasty, tired...physically and emotionally...and spiritually.  I really need some church.  I am gonna miss gettin up at 8 and doing Crossroads.  But oh well...if I can start going with my princess and some other peeps like Erinn and Jim, it could possibly feel like home anyways.  It should with or without them...I have family everywhere.  I just need some church and worship.  And some rest.  I have to go through my stuff and get rid of the jonk, figure out what I have, put it together, get what I can use for like 2 weeks (which can't be too much so I don't stress Jim out), move up to Jim's Wednesday, stopping by in the Boro to spend time with my princess, get up there and figure out how work is gonna...work.  Speaking of that, I'd better go do some...no rest for the weary...well thats a lie.  Check out Isaiah 40...He's still got me :) .

Not in a bad mood...not in a great mood...in a very weird mood!

Everythings just so unstable its hard to find constancy.  How 'bout I look to God, cause He's the true constancy in all this.  Him and Kelley.  Of course, my family has always done that as well.  Its just even in those things I am not supposed to find my peace...well, I trust my family and I definitely trust Kelley...I just trust them because I trust Him.  He is the one who gives the peace anyways.  It is foolish to think that just because God gives you a peace in something or someone that that thing is the one who blesses you with the peace.  I almost hate saying that to take away from how special my family and Kelley are...but God deserves all the glory and they both would agree with that one.  Well I do feel better in realizing that one...not that anything was really that wrong...honestly, I need some God time and I need some Kelley time.  Yarr...a pirate noise to send us off...

...I find this debatable as to whether I should even write here...but I had to write something, so this is it...btw this version of Pachelbels is crappy, its too fast...I guess I'll just write in my real journal...

You belong to God...to the creator of all good things.  Who made the foundation of the earth (Job 38:4), who chooses the appointed time (Psalm 75:2), who knows all of us, our thoughts, heart and the very nature of our being and from whom we cannot hide (Psalm 139), who is bigger than what we can even dream of (Isaiah 40:13-20).  Why does this matter...Matthew 6:25-34.  God's got you...just check out what He has in store for you in the Bible.  The more you figure out about Him, the less you have to worry about!

You belong to Him...that is who you are :) .

Not even sure why I started this one, prolly won't write in it alot.  I feel like the other one is mainly formal, so I guess I'll just talk on this one if I ever get the chance.  I prolly won't update it that much tho.  Same old stuff goin on right now...missing Kelley after she left for home.  Won't see her for a full week this time.  At least I don't have to wait two weeks!  Hopefully all the work I have to do will make the week go by pretty quickly.  Plus, I always have God right here with me :) !!!
